# Package manager: pnpm ONLY.
#
# pnpm-lock.yaml is DELIBERATELY tracked, not ignored. Every layer Dockerfile runs
# `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`, and .github/workflows/ci.yml caches on
# `${{ matrix.layer }}/pnpm-lock.yaml`. While those files were ignored, that install failed
# on every CI run before it ever reached `pnpm test` -- which is how a repo whose entry
# points and test suites were all broken still reported a green pipeline.
#
# npm lockfiles are ignored: two lockfiles for one package.json is two answers to
# "what version is installed", and the one nothing reads always wins the argument.
package-lock.json
**/package-lock.json